  "prompt": "What is a plant habitat?",
  "response": "A plant habitat is the natural environment where a specific plant species lives and grows. It includes various environmental factors such as:\n\n1. Soil type and composition\n2. Climate conditions (temperature, rainfall, humidity)\n3. Sunlight exposure\n4. Altitude\n5. Geographical location\n6. Surrounding vegetation and wildlife\n7. Water availability\n8. Terrain or landscape features\n\nDifferent plants have specific habitat requirements that support their survival and growth. For example:\n- Tropical rainforest plants need warm, humid conditions\n- Desert plants thrive in hot, dry environments\n- Alpine plants can survive in cold, rocky mountain regions\n- Aquatic plants live in water environments\n\nThe habitat provides the necessary resources and conditions for a plant to germinate, grow, reproduce, and complete its life cycle.",
